  "30 bones (clavicle + scapula + humerus + radius + ulna + 8 carpals + 5 metacarpals + 8 phalanges)": "",
  "36 bones (clavicle + scapula + humerus + radius + ulna + 10 carpals + 5 metacarpals + 16 phalanges)": "",
  "One complete upper limb has 32 bones: 2 in the pectoral girdle (clavicle and scapula), 1 humerus, 2 forearm bones (radius and ulna), 8 carpals, 5 metacarpals, and 14 phalanges.": "",
  "An obstetrician measures the pelvic dimensions of a pregnant patient using imaging to determine if a vaginal delivery is possible. The measurement shows a narrow pelvic inlet. What clinical concern does this raise?": "",
  "The patient's hip bones have not fully fused": "",
  "The sacrum is too large and will block the birth canal": "",
  "The baby will be born prematurely": "",
  "The narrow pelvic inlet may not allow the fetal head to pass through, potentially requiring a cesarean delivery": "",
  "A narrow pelvic inlet can prevent the passage of the fetal head through the birth canal during vaginal delivery, a condition known as cephalopelvic disproportion. If the pelvic dimensions are insufficient, a cesarean section may be necessary for safe delivery.": ""
